      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_The Globe and Mail - 2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_014_15",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "1. Each row and each column must contain the numbers 1 through 6 without repeating. 2.The numbers within the heavily outlined boxes, clled cages, must combine using the given operation (in any order) to produce the target numbers in the top-lefi corners. 3. Freebies: Fillin single-box cages with the numbers in the",
        "bbox": [
