        ],
        "order": 24
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_The Globe and Mail - 2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_014_21",
        "observed_type": "list",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "originally rousing one famous clown (6) 2 Unusually nice lad in charge of N Atlantic island (9) 3 Extremely concerned about upper-class celebrity's sauce (7) 4 Theme park feature's period of ups and downs (6-7) 5 University abandoning yearly record (5) 6 Fish having organs of sight, reportedly? (3) 7 Spice Gir upporting teachers' union (6) L2 Strange gap in Nel's wall surfacing (9) L4 Arouse trendy sweetheart (7) L5 Row involving a restaurant's first bill of fare (6) L6 Titled man losing heart in Greater London borough (6) L8 Some unfortunate Ethiopian's dentures, perhaps (5) 21 Health resort in southe Pennsylvania (3)",
        "bbox": [
          0.20833333333333334,
          0.5261691542288557,
          0.3475,
          0.7590049751243781
        ],
        "order": 26
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_The Globe and Mail - 2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_014_24",
        "observed_type": "image_caption",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "There are many worthwhile conventions that enable a good defensive pair to score all the tricks to which they're entitled. Some players ignore these con- ventions, relying more on in- stinct than science, but this is a dangerous way to play the game.",
        "bbox": [
          0.7866666666666666,
          0.5301492537313433,
          0.9658333333333333,
          0.5866666666666667
        ],
        "order": 29
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_The Globe and Mail - 2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_014_19",
        "observed_type": "list",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "1 Engineers involved with plant's rebirth (13) 8 South American guerrilla leader's second game (5) 9 Tenniel could be so merciful and forbearing (7) 10 Husband in motor publicity initially enduring mockery (7) 11 Failing of Scandinavian nomads, by the sound of it (5) 13 Subtraction of money? It's what we infer (9) 17 Racecourse a northerner identifies? (5) 19 Fellw appearing repeatedly with a leguminous plant (7) 20Look closely at creepy- crawly crossing entrance to park (7) 22 A legal right for a foreigner (5) 23 Boxer's dad securing time at last with rowing crew (13)",
        "bbox": [
          0.034166666666666665,
          0.5329353233830846,
          0.18666666666666668,
          0.7371144278606965
        ],
        "order": 30
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_The Globe and Mail - 2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_014_39",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Take the present deal, which features top-notch partnership defence. West leads a club, East winning dummy's queen with the ace. East, diagnosing the lead as a _possible singleton, returns the three of clubs, ruffed by est with the deuce.",
        "bbox": [
          0.7866666666666666,
          0.5862686567164179,
          0.9658333333333333,
          0.6360199004975124
        ],
        "order": 31
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_The Globe and Mail - 2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_014_40",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "East's return of the three, rather than just any club, is conventional. It says that, as be- tween hearts and diamonds, he would prefer that West lead the lower-ranking suit next. (Had East preferred a heart return, he would have led the eight of clubs to ask for the higher-ranking suit.)",
        "bbox": [
          0.7858333333333334,
          0.6364179104477612,
          0.9666666666666667,
          0.6981094527363184
        ],
        "order": 32
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_The Globe and Mail - 2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_014_43",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Accordingly, West leads the diamond three to East's queen and South's ace. Declarer plays a trump to dummy's jack and East's ace, and now East has a genuine problem.",
        "bbox": [
          0.7866666666666666,
          0.6981094527363184,
          0.9658333333333333,
          0.7355223880597015
        ],
        "order": 33
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_The Globe and Mail - 2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_014_41",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "If he thinks West has another trump, East should return a club; but if he thinks West has no more trumps, his best chance is a dia- mond return. with only his own 13 cards to rely on, East might easily go wrong and hand South the contract. But another con- vention, the trump echo, comes to his rescue.",
        "bbox": [
          0.7858333333333334,
          0.7355223880597015,
          0.9666666666666667,
          0.7976119402985075
        ],
        "order": 35
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_The Globe and Mail - 2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_014_28",
        "observed_type": "list",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "1 Tempted (7) 5 Bone of the ear (5) 8 Temporarily halted (2,3) 9 Knotty, twisted (7) 10 Practice of seeking to gain superiority over others (3-9) 12 Turn upside down or back to front (6) 14 Symptom of a cold (6) 17 Ufterly bffin (12) 21 Food addive code (1-6) 22 Growl menacingly (5) 23 Rested on one's patellae () 24(Ofa bathroom) accessibl from a bedroom (2,5)",
        "bbox": [
          0.035,
          0.7884577114427861,
          0.18,
          0.9194029850746268
        ],
        "order": 41
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_The Globe and Mail - 2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_014_30",
        "observed_type": "list",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "1 Pertaining to the financial system (8) 2 Fleeting moment (5) 3 Less expensive (7) 4 Folded corner of a page (3-3) 5 Douglas —, humorous science-fiction author (5) 6 Foxlike (7) 7 Children's board game(4) 11 Military wake-up call (8) 13 Business enterprise (7) 15 Agent of one's downfall( 7 16 Formal accusation made against a suspect (6) 18 Extent, scope (5) 19 Spicy ball f chopped vegetables fried in batter (5) 20 Pack of cards(4)",
        "bbox": [
          0.20416666666666666,
          0.7884577114427861,
          0.3525,
          0.940497512437811
        ],
        "order": 42
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_The Globe and Mail - 2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_014_42",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "West's ruff with the two of spades, followed later by the play of the four, denies a hold- ing of three trumps. If west had started with the 6-4-2, for ex- ample, he would have ruffed the club at trick two with the four and later played the deuce to indicate possession of a third trump.",
        "bbox": [
          0.7858333333333334,
          0.7976119402985075,
          0.9666666666666667,
          0.8597014925373134
        ],
        "order": 43
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_The Globe and Mail - 2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_014_44",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "East therefore returns a dia- mond at trick five, and four spades goes down two. With a club return, South makes the contract.",
        "bbox": [
          0.7866666666666666,
          0.8597014925373134,
          0.9658333333333333,
          0.8911442786069652
        ],
        "order": 44
      }
